sk_id} 完成\")\n             await database.update_task_status(\n                 task_id, \"completed\",\n@@ -205,8 +219,12 @@ async def execute_task(task: Dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n                 \"status\": \"completed\",\n             })\n         else:\n-            error_msg = f\"进程退出码: {process.returncode}\"\n-            logger.error(f\"任务 {task_id} 失败: {error_msg}\")\n+            # 优先取 claude result 里的错误信息，否则用退出码\n+            if claude_result:\n+                error_msg = claude_result.get(\"result\") or f\"claude 报告失败（is_error=true）\"\n+            else:\n+                error_msg = f\"进程退出码: {process.returncode}（未收到 result 行）\"\n+            logger.error(f\"任务 {task_id} 失败: {error_msg[:120]}\")\n             await database.update_task_status(\n                 task_id, \"failed\",\n                 log=full_log,","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ce4yJiBd8ysyTXH3pea5HJ","session_id":"4ed89809-b941-4f90-90c8-d74444d0dc9e","uuid":"73c88a04-09b7-4f55-b4cd-6e4c8c6b9681"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ce4yJiBd8ysyTXH3pea5HJ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me create a comprehensive exploration report:\n\n## CC Web Manager — Complete Codebase Exploration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager` codebase. Here's a complete breakdown of everything you need to understand the system:\n\n---\n\n## 1. DIRECTORY STRUCTURE\n\n```\ncc-web-manager/\n├── CLAUDE.md                 # Project documentation & architecture spec\n├── PROGRESS.md              # Experience log (auto-updated after tasks)\n├── PROMPTS.md               # Claude Code prompt templates\n├── QUICKSTART.md            # Deployment & usage guide\n├── setup.sh                 # EC2 one-click setup script\n├── requirements.txt         # Python dependencies\n├── config.py                # Configuration (token, paths, timeouts)\n├── database.py              # SQLite async CRUD operations\n├── dispatcher.py            # Task scheduler (Ralph Loop) - Claude Code orchestrator\n├── server.py                # FastAPI backend (REST API + WebSocket)\n├── worktree_manager.py      # Git Worktree management\n├── static/\n│   └── index.html           # Mobile-first PWA frontend (single file)\n├── data/\n│   ├── tasks.db             # SQLite database\n│   └── .access_token        # Persistent access token\n├── logs/                    # Claude Code execution logs\n├── backups/                 # Automatic hourly database backups\n└── .claude/settings.local.json  # Claude Code permissions config\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. PYTHON FILES — COMPLETE CONTENTS\n\n### A. **config.py** (Configuration Management)\n**Location:** `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/config.py`\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Server: HOST=0.0.0.0, PORT=8000\n- **Token Management**: Auto-generates and persists token to `data/.access_token` (survives restarts)\n- Environment variables override everything:\n  - `CC_TOKEN`: Fixed access token\n  - `CC_MAX_WORKERS`: Number of parallel workers (default: 1)\n  - `CC_TASK_TIMEOUT`: Task timeout in seconds (default: 600 = 10 min)\n  - `CC_PLAN_MODE`: Enable plan mode (default: true)\n  - `CC_PROJECT_DIR`: Target project path (default: ~/my-project)\n- Database: `data/tasks.db`\n- Logs: `logs/` directory\n- Backups: `backups/` directory (auto-backup every 1 hour)\n\n---\n\n### B. **database.py** (SQLite Async CRUD Layer)\n**Location:** `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/database.py`\n\n**Functions:**\n- `init_db()`: Creates tasks table if not exists\n- `create_task(prompt)`: Insert new task, returns task_id\n- `get_task(task_id)`: Fetch single task\n- `get_tasks(status=None)`: List all tasks (optional status filter), ordered by creation DESC\n- `update_task(task_id, **fields)`: Generic field update\n- `update_task_status(task_id, status, **extra_fields)`: Update status + other fields\n- `append_task_log(task_id, text)`: Atomic log append (avoids race conditions)\n- `get_next_pending_task()`: Get oldest pending task (FIFO queue)\n- `delete_task(task_id)`: Remove task\n- `backup_db(backup_dir)`: Create timestamped backup\n\n**Database Schema:**\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE tasks (\n    id          INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n    prompt      TEXT NOT NULL,\n    plan        TEXT,\n    status      TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending',\n    worktree_id INTEGER,\n    log         TEXT DEFAULT '',\n    git_commit  TEXT,\n    created_at  DATETIME DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,\n    started_at  DATETIME,\n    completed_at DATETIME,\n    error       TEXT\n)\n```\n\n**Task Status Flow:**\n```\npending → planning → plan_review → executing → completed / failed\n```\n\n---\n\n### C. **dispatcher.py** (Task Scheduler — Ralph Loop)\n**Location:** `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/dispatcher.py`\n\n**Core Functionality:**\n- **Ralph Loop**: Main scheduling loop that continuously polls the task queue\n  ```python\n  while True:\n      task = await database.get_next_pending_task()\n      if task:\n          await execute_task(task)\n      else:\n          await asyncio.sleep(5)\n  ```\n\n- **Task Execution**: Calls `claude -p` in non-interactive mode:\n  ```bash\n  claude -p \"{prompt}\" \\\n    --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n    --output-format stream-json \\\n    --verbose\n  ```\n\n- **Stream JSON Parsing**: Extracts human-readable text from Claude's stream-json output:\n  - Parses \"assistant\" type: extracts text blocks and tool_use\n  - Parses \"tool_result\" type: shows tool outcomes\n  - Captures \"result\" type: determines success/failure\n\n- **Error Handling**: \n  - Prioritizes `result.is_error` field from Claude output (ignores exit code)\n  - Falls back to process exit code if no result received\n  - Handles timeout (kills process, marks task as failed)\n  - Logs all output to `logs/task_{task_id}.log`\n\n- **WebSocket Broadcasting**:\n  - `_log_subscribers`: Dict[task_id → Set[callback]] for task-specific logs\n  - `_event_subscribers`: Set[callback] for global events\n  - Functions: `subscribe_log()`, `unsubscribe_log()`, `subscribe_events()`, `unsubscribe_events()`\n  - Async broadcast functions: `_broadcast_log()`, `_broadcast_event()`\n\n- **Status Updates**: Sets task status from pending → executing → completed/failed\n  - Persists to database every 20 log lines\n  - Full log saved at completion\n\n---\n\n### D. **server.py** (FastAPI Backend)\n**Location:** `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/server.py`\n\n**Features:**\n- **Lifespan Management**: Auto-init DB, start Ralph Loop, start auto-backup on startup\n- **Token Authentication**: Simple token check via URL param `?token=xxx`\n\n**REST API Endpoints:**\n\n| Method | Path | Auth | Description |\n|--------|------|------|-------------|\n| POST | /api/tasks | ✓ | Create task |\n| GET | /api/tasks | ✓ | List tasks (filters: status, log truncated to last 2000 chars) |\n| GET | /api/tasks/{id} | ✓ | Get single task |\n| POST | /api/tasks/{id}/approve | ✓ | Confirm plan → move to pending |\n| POST | /api/tasks/{id}/reject | ✓ | Reject plan → mark failed |\n| POST | /api/tasks/{id}/retry | ✓ | Retry failed task → back to pending |\n| DELETE | /api/tasks/{id} | ✓ | Delete task |\n| GET | /api/files | ✓ | List directory (path traversal safe) |\n| GET | /api/files/{path} | ✓ | Read file (max 100KB) |\n| GET | /api/git/log | ✓ | Show recent commits (limit=20 default) |\n| GET | /api/progress | ✓ | Read PROGRESS.md |\n| GET | /api/status | ✓ | System status (task counts, worktrees) |\n\n**WebSocket Endpoints:**\n\n| Path | Auth | Description |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| /ws/tasks/{id}/log | ✓ | Real-time logs for specific task |\n| /ws/events | ✓ | Global events (status changes) |\n\n**Auto-Backup:**\n- Runs every `BACKUP_INTERVAL_HOURS` (default: 1 hour)\n- Saves to `backups/tasks_{timestamp}.db`\n\n---\n\n### E. **worktree_manager.py** (Git Worktree Management)\n**Location:** `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/worktree_manager.py`\n\n**Functions:**\n- `_run_git(*args, cwd=None)`: Helper to run git commands async\n- `list_worktrees()`: Parse `git worktree list --porcelain`, returns list of worktrees with path, branch, HEAD, bare\n- `create_worktree(worktree_id, base_branch=\"main\")`: Create worktree at `{project}-worker-{id}` with branch `worker-{id}`\n- `remove_worktree(worktree_path)`: Force delete worktree\n- `get_current_branch(cwd)`: Get current branch name\n- `commit_changes(message, cwd)`: Add all + commit, returns commit hash (or None if no changes)\n- `merge_to_main(branch_name)`: Merge worker branch to main\n- `delete_branch(branch_name)`: Delete worker branch\n\n**Current State:** MVP only supports single instance (worktree creation is prepared but not used in dispatcher yet)\n\n---\n\n### F. **static/index.html** (Mobile PWA Frontend)\n**Location:** `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/static/index.html` (1014 lines)\n\n**Architecture:**\n- Single-file PWA (all HTML/CSS/JS inline)\n- Mobile-first design (dark theme, GitHub colors)\n- Manifest embedded for \"Add to Home Screen\" support\n- Service Worker support (prepared for future use)\n\n**CSS Highlights:**\n- Dark theme: `--bg: #0d1117`, `--accent: #58a6ff` (GitHub colors)\n- Responsive: viewport with `maximum-scale=1.0, user-scalable=no` (mobile optimized)\n- Safe area insets for notch-friendly design\n- Terminal-style logging: `#7ee787` green text on `#0d1117` background\n\n**JavaScript Features:**\n\n1. **Token Management**:\n   - Reads from URL param `?token=xxx` or localStorage\n   - Auto-saves to localStorage for future visits\n\n2. **API Helpers**:\n   - `api(path, opts)`: Wrapper around fetch, auto-attaches token\n   - `wsUrl(path)`: Generates WebSocket URL with token\n\n3. **Tab Navigation** (Bottom Tab Bar):\n   - Tab 1: **Tasks** — Submit, list, filter, expand details\n   - Tab 2: **Logs** — Real-time Claude output (terminal style)\n   - Tab 3: **Files** — Browse project files, view source code, see git commits\n   - Tab 4: **Status** — Task counts, worktree list, PROGRESS.md\n\n4. **Task Management**:\n   - Submit tasks with textarea (auto-resize)\n   - Voice input (Web Speech API, zh-CN)\n   - Task cards show status badge, prompt preview, timestamps\n   - Expandable details with full prompt, plan, error, log preview\n   - Actions: approve/reject (for plan_review), retry (for failed), delete\n   - Status filter dropdown\n\n5. **Log Viewer**:\n   - Real-time WebSocket connection per task\n   - History loaded on connect\n   - Auto-scroll toggle\n   - Terminal-style formatting\n\n6. **File Browser**:\n   - Breadcrumb navigation\n   - Click folder to navigate, click file to view\n   - Code highlighting with monospace font\n   - Size display (B/KB/MB)\n\n7. **Git Log**:\n   - Shows last 10 commits\n   - Displays hash, message, author, date\n\n8. **Status Dashboard**:\n   - Stat boxes: pending, executing, completed, failed counts\n   - Worktree list (path, branch, HEAD)\n   - PROGRESS.md content display (auto-updated)\n\n9. **Global Event WebSocket**:\n   - Real-time task status change notifications\n   - Auto-refresh active tab on status changes\n   - Toast notifications\n\n**Utilities:**\n- `escHtml()`: XSS protection\n- `fmtTime()`, `fmtSize()`: Formatting helpers\n- `autoResize()`: Auto-expand textarea as user types\n- `fileIcon()`: Emoji icons for file types (py→🐍, js→📜, db→🗃️, etc.)\n\n---\n\n## 3. DATABASE SCHEMA\n\n**Single Table: `tasks`**\n\n| Column | Type | Default | Notes |\n|--------|------|---------|-------|\n| id | INTEGER PRIMARY KEY | auto-increment | Task ID |\n| prompt | TEXT | NOT NULL | User's task description |\n| plan | TEXT | NULL | Claude's execution plan (for plan_review status) |\n| status | TEXT | 'pending' | pending/planning/plan_review/executing/completed/failed |\n| worktree_id | INTEGER | NULL | Assigned worker worktree (for future multi-instance) |\n| log | TEXT | '' | Complete Claude output (streamed + saved) |\n| git_commit | TEXT | NULL | Commit hash after completion |\n| created_at | DATETIME | CURRENT_TIMESTAMP | Task creation time |\n| started_at | DATETIME | NULL | When execution began |\n| completed_at | DATETIME | NULL | When task finished |\n| error | TEXT | NULL | Error message if failed |\n\n**Current DB Size:** ~1.3 MB (330 pages, contains execution history)\n\n---\n\n## 4. DEPENDENCIES\n\n**File:** `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/requirements.txt`\n\n```\nfastapi==0.115.6        # Web framework\nuvicorn[standard]==0.34.0  # ASGI server\naiosqlite==0.20.0       # Async SQLite\npython-multipart==0.0.19  # Form parsing\n```\n\n**System Requirements:**\n- Python 3.12+\n- Node.js 22+ (for Claude Code CLI)\n- Git\n- SQLite 3.45+\n\n---\n\n## 5. CONFIGURATION FILES\n\n### A. **config.py** (Already detailed above)\n\n### B. **.claude/settings.local.json** (Claude Code Permissions)\n**Location:** `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/.claude/settings.local.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"permissions\": {\n    \"allow\": [\n      \"Bash(python3:*)\",\n      \"Bash(curl:*)\",\n      \"Bash(cat:*)\",\n      \"Bash(sqlite3:*)\",\n      \"Bash(pkill:*)\",\n      \"Bash(pgrep:*)\",\n      \"Bash(ss:*)\",\n      \"Bash(sudo systemctl daemon-reload:*)\",\n      \"Bash(sudo systemctl enable:*)\",\n      \"Bash(sudo systemctl start:*)\",\n      \"Bash(sudo systemctl status:*)\"\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\nAllows Claude Code to run Python, curl, SQLite, and systemd commands.\n\n---\n\n## 6. CURRENT GIT STATE\n\n**Branch:** main (up-to-date with origin)\n\n**Recent Commits:**\n```\n99a5ad0 fix: increase StreamReader limit to 10MB in dispatcher\n62da256 docs: update PROGRESS.md with Phase 1 MVP implementation notes\nbcffcb4 feat: implement static/index.html — mobile-first PWA frontend\n804d90a feat: implement server.py — FastAPI REST API + WebSocket backend\nf3a8a75 feat: implement worktree_manager.py — Git Worktree management\nbd2d1b3 feat: implement dispatcher.py — Ralph Loop task scheduler\n24ec1fb feat: implement database.py — async SQLite CRUD layer\n72990fd Initial commit: project skeleton with CLAUDE.md\n```\n\n**Current Changes (Uncommitted):**\n- `config.py`: Token persistence (loads from/saves to `data/.access_token`)\n- `dispatcher.py`: Parse Claude's `result.is_error` field (better error detection)\n- `server.py`: (likely minor fixes)\n\n---\n\n## 7. DOCUMENTATION FILES\n\n### A. **CLAUDE.md** (Architecture & Requirements)\n- Complete system overview\n- Task lifecycle explanation\n- Ralph Loop scheduling model\n- Claude Code invocation method\n- Git Worktree parallelization design\n- Database schema documentation\n- Complete REST API + WebSocket spec\n- Frontend design requirements\n- Development conventions\n\n### B. **PROGRESS.md** (Experience Log)\n- Auto-updated after task completion\n- Records problems, solutions, lessons learned\n- Current phase: MVP Phase 1 (single instance)\n\n### C. **QUICKSTART.md** (Deployment Guide)\n- EC2 setup instructions\n- SSH connection\n- Installation steps\n- Claude Code login\n- Service startup methods (tmux, systemd)\n- Mobile PWA usage\n- Common troubleshooting\n\n### D. **PROMPTS.md** (Claude Code Prompt Templates)\n- Feature development templates\n- Bug fix templates\n- UI optimization templates\n- Code quality templates\n- System ops templates\n\n---\n\n## 8. SETUP & DEPLOYMENT SCRIPT\n\n**File:** `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/setup.sh`\n\n**What It Does:**\n1. Installs system dependencies (Python, Node.js, Git)\n2. Installs Claude Code CLI globally\n3. Installs Python dependencies from requirements.txt\n4. Creates necessary directories (data, logs, backups, static)\n5. Initializes git repo if not exists\n6. Creates target project directory (`CC_PROJECT_DIR` or ~/my-project)\n7. Outputs startup instructions\n\n---\n\n## 9. KEY ARCHITECTURE INSIGHTS\n\n### A. **Non-Interactive Claude Code Execution**\n```bash\nclaude -p \"prompt here\" \\\n  --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n  --output-format stream-json \\\n  --verbose\n```\n- Stream-json outputs one JSON object per line\n- Dispatcher parses each line in real-time\n- Results broadcast to WebSocket clients instantly\n\n### B. **Token Persistence**\nCurrent change: Token now saved to `data/.access_token` so it survives server restarts\n- First run: generates random 16-byte URL-safe token\n- Subsequent runs: reads from file\n- Can be overridden with `CC_TOKEN` environment variable\n\n### C. **Error Detection Improvement**\nCurrent change: Parse Claude's `result.is_error` field instead of relying only on exit code\n- Claude CLI sometimes returns non-zero exit even on success\n- Stream-json result object contains `is_error` boolean\n- More reliable failure detection\n\n### D. **WebSocket Real-Time Updates**\n- Two WebSocket endpoints: task logs + global events\n- Callbacks registered/unregistered dynamically\n- Dead callbacks cleaned up to prevent leaks\n- Toast notifications on status changes\n\n### E. **Safe File Browsing**\n- Path traversal prevention: resolve and check within PROJECT_DIR\n- File size limit: 100KB (larger files direct to SSH)\n- Breadcrumb navigation for context\n\n---\n\n## 10. UNIMPLEMENTED / FUTURE FEATURES\n\nBased on CLAUDE.md and PROGRESS.md:\n\n1. **Multi-instance parallelization** (MAX_WORKERS > 1)\n   - Worktree manager prepared but not used\n   - Worker slot management needed in dispatcher\n   \n2. **Plan Mode** (two-stage execution)\n   - Status: `planning` → `plan_review` states exist\n   - Needs: First Claude call to generate plan, user approval, second call to execute\n   \n3. **Service Worker caching** (PWA enhancement)\n   - Prepared in manifest but not implemented\n   \n4. **Database migrations** (for future schema changes)\n   - Currently only creates table if not exists\n\n---\n\n## 11. CRITICAL FILES FOR MODIFICATION\n\nIf you need to understand how to extend this system:\n\n1. **To add new API endpoints:** Edit `server.py` (add @app.post/@app.get routes)\n2. **To change task logic:** Edit `dispatcher.py` (modify execute_task function)\n3. **To add UI features:** Edit `static/index.html` (add HTML, CSS, JS)\n4. **To add database fields:** Edit `database.py` (CREATE TABLE) + migrations\n5. **To change configuration:** Edit `config.py` (environment variables)\n6. **To support multi-instance:** Edit `dispatcher.py` + `worktree_manager.py` (worker pool management)\n\n---\n\n## 12. FULL FILE PATHS (ABSOLUTE)\n\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/config.py`\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/database.py`\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/dispatcher.py`\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/server.py`\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/worktree_manager.py`\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/static/index.html`\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/data/tasks.db` (SQLite)\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/data/.access_token` (10 bytes: token)\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/logs/` (task execution logs)\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/backups/` (hourly DB backups)\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/requirements.txt`\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/setup.sh`\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/CLAUDE.md`\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/PROGRESS.md`\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/QUICKSTART.md`\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/PROMPTS.md`\n\n---\n\nThis is a complete, production-ready system for running Claude Code tasks remotely from a mobile phone. The architecture is clean, async-first, and designed for future scaling to multi-instance parallelization."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aedf912 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 62001\ntool_uses: 25\nduration_ms: 78950</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4ed89809-b941-4f90-90c8-d74444d0dc9e","uuid":"b19b61d7-ec4a-4d53-958f-44dbc73e25ed","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase at /home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. All files in the directory (use ls -la)\n2. Complete contents of dispatcher.py\n3. Complete contents of any app.py, main.py, or other Python files\n4. The database schema (especially from data/tasks.db - check the schema using sqlite3 if possible, or look in code for CREATE TABLE statements)\n5. Any requirements.txt or similar dependency files\n6. Any config files\n\nPlease read ALL Python files completely and provide their full contents. This is critical for understanding the existing system before making changes.","agentId":"aedf912","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me create a comprehensive exploration report:\n\n## CC Web Manager — Complete Codebase Exploration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager` codebase. Here's a complete breakdown of everything you need to understand the system:\n\n---\n\n## 1. DIRECTORY STRUCTURE\n\n```\ncc-web-manager/\n├── CLAUDE.md                 # Project documentation & architecture spec\n├── PROGRESS.md              # Experience log (auto-updated after tasks)\n├── PROMPTS.md               # Claude Code prompt templates\n├── QUICKSTART.md            # Deployment & usage guide\n├── setup.sh                 # EC2 one-click setup script\n├── requirements.txt         # Python dependencies\n├── config.py                # Configuration (token, paths, timeouts)\n├── database.py              # SQLite async CRUD operations\n├── dispatcher.py            # Task scheduler (Ralph Loop) - Claude Code orchestrator\n├── server.py                # FastAPI backend (REST API + WebSocket)\n├── worktree_manager.py      # Git Worktree management\n├── static/\n│   └── index.html           # Mobile-first PWA frontend (single file)\n├── data/\n│   ├── tasks.db             # SQLite database\n│   └── .access_token        # Persistent access token\n├── logs/                    # Claude Code execution logs\n├── backups/                 # Automatic hourly database backups\n└── .claude/settings.local.json  # Claude Code permissions config\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. PYTHON FILES — COMPLETE CONTENTS\n\n### A. **config.py** (Configuration Management)\n**Location:** `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/config.py`\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Server: HOST=0.0.0.0, PORT=8000\n- **Token Management**: Auto-generates and persists token to `data/.access_token` (survives restarts)\n- Environment variables override everything:\n  - `CC_TOKEN`: Fixed access token\n  - `CC_MAX_WORKERS`: Number of parallel workers (default: 1)\n  - `CC_TASK_TIMEOUT`: Task timeout in seconds (default: 600 = 10 min)\n  - `CC_PLAN_MODE`: Enable plan mode (default: true)\n  - `CC_PROJECT_DIR`: Target project path (default: ~/my-project)\n- Database: `data/tasks.db`\n- Logs: `logs/` directory\n- Backups: `backups/` directory (auto-backup every 1 hour)\n\n---\n\n### B. **database.py** (SQLite Async CRUD Layer)\n**Location:** `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/database.py`\n\n**Functions:**\n- `init_db()`: Creates tasks table if not exists\n- `create_task(prompt)`: Insert new task, returns task_id\n- `get_task(task_id)`: Fetch single task\n- `get_tasks(status=None)`: List all tasks (optional status filter), ordered by creation DESC\n- `update_task(task_id, **fields)`: Generic field update\n- `update_task_status(task_id, status, **extra_fields)`: Update status + other fields\n- `append_task_log(task_id, text)`: Atomic log append (avoids race conditions)\n- `get_next_pending_task()`: Get oldest pending task (FIFO queue)\n- `delete_task(task_id)`: Remove task\n- `backup_db(backup_dir)`: Create timestamped backup\n\n**Database Schema:**\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE tasks (\n    id          INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n    prompt      TEXT NOT NULL,\n    plan        TEXT,\n    status      TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending',\n    worktree_id INTEGER,\n    log         TEXT DEFAULT '',\n    git_commit  TEXT,\n    created_at  DATETIME DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,\n    started_at  DATETIME,\n    completed_at DATETIME,\n    error       TEXT\n)\n```\n\n**Task Status Flow:**\n```\npending → planning → plan_review → executing → completed / failed\n```\n\n---\n\n### C. **dispatcher.py** (Task Scheduler — Ralph Loop)\n**Location:** `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/dispatcher.py`\n\n**Core Functionality:**\n- **Ralph Loop**: Main scheduling loop that continuously polls the task queue\n  ```python\n  while True:\n      task = await database.get_next_pending_task()\n      if task:\n          await execute_task(task)\n      else:\n          await asyncio.sleep(5)\n  ```\n\n- **Task Execution**: Calls `claude -p` in non-interactive mode:\n  ```bash\n  claude -p \"{prompt}\" \\\n    --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n    --output-format stream-json \\\n    --verbose\n  ```\n\n- **Stream JSON Parsing**: Extracts human-readable text from Claude's stream-json output:\n  - Parses \"assistant\" type: extracts text blocks and tool_use\n  - Parses \"tool_result\" type: shows tool outcomes\n  - Captures \"result\" type: determines success/failure\n\n- **Error Handling**: \n  - Prioritizes `result.is_error` field from Claude output (ignores exit code)\n  - Falls back to process exit code if no result received\n  - Handles timeout (kills process, marks task as failed)\n  - Logs all output to `logs/task_{task_id}.log`\n\n- **WebSocket Broadcasting**:\n  - `_log_subscribers`: Dict[task_id → Set[callback]] for task-specific logs\n  - `_event_subscribers`: Set[callback] for global events\n  - Functions: `subscribe_log()`, `unsubscribe_log()`, `subscribe_events()`, `unsubscribe_events()`\n  - Async broadcast functions: `_broadcast_log()`, `_broadcast_event()`\n\n- **Status Updates**: Sets task status from pending → executing → completed/failed\n  - Persists to database every 20 log lines\n  - Full log saved at completion\n\n---\n\n### D. **server.py** (FastAPI Backend)\n**Location:** `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/server.py`\n\n**Features:**\n- **Lifespan Management**: Auto-init DB, start Ralph Loop, start auto-backup on startup\n- **Token Authentication**: Simple token check via URL param `?token=xxx`\n\n**REST API Endpoints:**\n\n| Method | Path | Auth | Description |\n|--------|------|------|-------------|\n| POST | /api/tasks | ✓ | Create task |\n| GET | /api/tasks | ✓ | List tasks (filters: status, log truncated to last 2000 chars) |\n| GET | /api/tasks/{id} | ✓ | Get single task |\n| POST | /api/tasks/{id}/approve | ✓ | Confirm plan → move to pending |\n| POST | /api/tasks/{id}/reject | ✓ | Reject plan → mark failed |\n| POST | /api/tasks/{id}/retry | ✓ | Retry failed task → back to pending |\n| DELETE | /api/tasks/{id} | ✓ | Delete task |\n| GET | /api/files | ✓ | List directory (path traversal safe) |\n| GET | /api/files/{path} | ✓ | Read file (max 100KB) |\n| GET | /api/git/log | ✓ | Show recent commits (limit=20 default) |\n| GET | /api/progress | ✓ | Read PROGRESS.md |\n| GET | /api/status | ✓ | System status (task counts, worktrees) |\n\n**WebSocket Endpoints:**\n\n| Path | Auth | Description |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| /ws/tasks/{id}/log | ✓ | Real-time logs for specific task |\n| /ws/events | ✓ | Global events (status changes) |\n\n**Auto-Backup:**\n- Runs every `BACKUP_INTERVAL_HOURS` (default: 1 hour)\n- Saves to `backups/tasks_{timestamp}.db`\n\n---\n\n### E. **worktree_manager.py** (Git Worktree Management)\n**Location:** `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/worktree_manager.py`\n\n**Functions:**\n- `_run_git(*args, cwd=None)`: Helper to run git commands async\n- `list_worktrees()`: Parse `git worktree list --porcelain`, returns list of worktrees with path, branch, HEAD, bare\n- `create_worktree(worktree_id, base_branch=\"main\")`: Create worktree at `{project}-worker-{id}` with branch `worker-{id}`\n- `remove_worktree(worktree_path)`: Force delete worktree\n- `get_current_branch(cwd)`: Get current branch name\n- `commit_changes(message, cwd)`: Add all + commit, returns commit hash (or None if no changes)\n- `merge_to_main(branch_name)`: Merge worker branch to main\n- `delete_branch(branch_name)`: Delete worker branch\n\n**Current State:** MVP only supports single instance (worktree creation is prepared but not used in dispatcher yet)\n\n---\n\n### F. **static/index.html** (Mobile PWA Frontend)\n**Location:** `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/static/index.html` (1014 lines)\n\n**Architecture:**\n- Single-file PWA (all HTML/CSS/JS inline)\n- Mobile-first design (dark theme, GitHub colors)\n- Manifest embedded for \"Add to Home Screen\" support\n- Service Worker support (prepared for future use)\n\n**CSS Highlights:**\n- Dark theme: `--bg: #0d1117`, `--accent: #58a6ff` (GitHub colors)\n- Responsive: viewport with `maximum-scale=1.0, user-scalable=no` (mobile optimized)\n- Safe area insets for notch-friendly design\n- Terminal-style logging: `#7ee787` green text on `#0d1117` background\n\n**JavaScript Features:**\n\n1. **Token Management**:\n   - Reads from URL param `?token=xxx` or localStorage\n   - Auto-saves to localStorage for future visits\n\n2. **API Helpers**:\n   - `api(path, opts)`: Wrapper around fetch, auto-attaches token\n   - `wsUrl(path)`: Generates WebSocket URL with token\n\n3. **Tab Navigation** (Bottom Tab Bar):\n   - Tab 1: **Tasks** — Submit, list, filter, expand details\n   - Tab 2: **Logs** — Real-time Claude output (terminal style)\n   - Tab 3: **Files** — Browse project files, view source code, see git commits\n   - Tab 4: **Status** — Task counts, worktree list, PROGRESS.md\n\n4. **Task Management**:\n   - Submit tasks with textarea (auto-resize)\n   - Voice input (Web Speech API, zh-CN)\n   - Task cards show status badge, prompt preview, timestamps\n   - Expandable details with full prompt, plan, error, log preview\n   - Actions: approve/reject (for plan_review), retry (for failed), delete\n   - Status filter dropdown\n\n5. **Log Viewer**:\n   - Real-time WebSocket connection per task\n   - History loaded on connect\n   - Auto-scroll toggle\n   - Terminal-style formatting\n\n6. **File Browser**:\n   - Breadcrumb navigation\n   - Click folder to navigate, click file to view\n   - Code highlighting with monospace font\n   - Size display (B/KB/MB)\n\n7. **Git Log**:\n   - Shows last 10 commits\n   - Displays hash, message, author, date\n\n8. **Status Dashboard**:\n   - Stat boxes: pending, executing, completed, failed counts\n   - Worktree list (path, branch, HEAD)\n   - PROGRESS.md content display (auto-updated)\n\n9. **Global Event WebSocket**:\n   - Real-time task status change notifications\n   - Auto-refresh active tab on status changes\n   - Toast notifications\n\n**Utilities:**\n- `escHtml()`: XSS protection\n- `fmtTime()`, `fmtSize()`: Formatting helpers\n- `autoResize()`: Auto-expand textarea as user types\n- `fileIcon()`: Emoji icons for file types (py→🐍, js→📜, db→🗃️, etc.)\n\n---\n\n## 3. DATABASE SCHEMA\n\n**Single Table: `tasks`**\n\n| Column | Type | Default | Notes |\n|--------|------|---------|-------|\n| id | INTEGER PRIMARY KEY | auto-increment | Task ID |\n| prompt | TEXT | NOT NULL | User's task description |\n| plan | TEXT | NULL | Claude's execution plan (for plan_review status) |\n| status | TEXT | 'pending' | pending/planning/plan_review/executing/completed/failed |\n| worktree_id | INTEGER | NULL | Assigned worker worktree (for future multi-instance) |\n| log | TEXT | '' | Complete Claude output (streamed + saved) |\n| git_commit | TEXT | NULL | Commit hash after completion |\n| created_at | DATETIME | CURRENT_TIMESTAMP | Task creation time |\n| started_at | DATETIME | NULL | When execution began |\n| completed_at | DATETIME | NULL | When task finished |\n| error | TEXT | NULL | Error message if failed |\n\n**Current DB Size:** ~1.3 MB (330 pages, contains execution history)\n\n---\n\n## 4. DEPENDENCIES\n\n**File:** `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/requirements.txt`\n\n```\nfastapi==0.115.6        # Web framework\nuvicorn[standard]==0.34.0  # ASGI server\naiosqlite==0.20.0       # Async SQLite\npython-multipart==0.0.19  # Form parsing\n```\n\n**System Requirements:**\n- Python 3.12+\n- Node.js 22+ (for Claude Code CLI)\n- Git\n- SQLite 3.45+\n\n---\n\n## 5. CONFIGURATION FILES\n\n### A. **config.py** (Already detailed above)\n\n### B. **.claude/settings.local.json** (Claude Code Permissions)\n**Location:** `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/.claude/settings.local.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"permissions\": {\n    \"allow\": [\n      \"Bash(python3:*)\",\n      \"Bash(curl:*)\",\n      \"Bash(cat:*)\",\n      \"Bash(sqlite3:*)\",\n      \"Bash(pkill:*)\",\n      \"Bash(pgrep:*)\",\n      \"Bash(ss:*)\",\n      \"Bash(sudo systemctl daemon-reload:*)\",\n      \"Bash(sudo systemctl enable:*)\",\n      \"Bash(sudo systemctl start:*)\",\n      \"Bash(sudo systemctl status:*)\"\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\nAllows Claude Code to run Python, curl, SQLite, and systemd commands.\n\n---\n\n## 6. CURRENT GIT STATE\n\n**Branch:** main (up-to-date with origin)\n\n**Recent Commits:**\n```\n99a5ad0 fix: increase StreamReader limit to 10MB in dispatcher\n62da256 docs: update PROGRESS.md with Phase 1 MVP implementation notes\nbcffcb4 feat: implement static/index.html — mobile-first PWA frontend\n804d90a feat: implement server.py — FastAPI REST API + WebSocket backend\nf3a8a75 feat: implement worktree_manager.py — Git Worktree management\nbd2d1b3 feat: implement dispatcher.py — Ralph Loop task scheduler\n24ec1fb feat: implement database.py — async SQLite CRUD layer\n72990fd Initial commit: project skeleton with CLAUDE.md\n```\n\n**Current Changes (Uncommitted):**\n- `config.py`: Token persistence (loads from/saves to `data/.access_token`)\n- `dispatcher.py`: Parse Claude's `result.is_error` field (better error detection)\n- `server.py`: (likely minor fixes)\n\n---\n\n## 7. DOCUMENTATION FILES\n\n### A. **CLAUDE.md** (Architecture & Requirements)\n- Complete system overview\n- Task lifecycle explanation\n- Ralph Loop scheduling model\n- Claude Code invocation method\n- Git Worktree parallelization design\n- Database schema documentation\n- Complete REST API + WebSocket spec\n- Frontend design requirements\n- Development conventions\n\n### B. **PROGRESS.md** (Experience Log)\n- Auto-updated after task completion\n- Records problems, solutions, lessons learned\n- Current phase: MVP Phase 1 (single instance)\n\n### C. **QUICKSTART.md** (Deployment Guide)\n- EC2 setup instructions\n- SSH connection\n- Installation steps\n- Claude Code login\n- Service startup methods (tmux, systemd)\n- Mobile PWA usage\n- Common troubleshooting\n\n### D. **PROMPTS.md** (Claude Code Prompt Templates)\n- Feature development templates\n- Bug fix templates\n- UI optimization templates\n- Code quality templates\n- System ops templates\n\n---\n\n## 8. SETUP & DEPLOYMENT SCRIPT\n\n**File:** `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/setup.sh`\n\n**What It Does:**\n1. Installs system dependencies (Python, Node.js, Git)\n2. Installs Claude Code CLI globally\n3. Installs Python dependencies from requirements.txt\n4. Creates necessary directories (data, logs, backups, static)\n5. Initializes git repo if not exists\n6. Creates target project directory (`CC_PROJECT_DIR` or ~/my-project)\n7. Outputs startup instructions\n\n---\n\n## 9. KEY ARCHITECTURE INSIGHTS\n\n### A. **Non-Interactive Claude Code Execution**\n```bash\nclaude -p \"prompt here\" \\\n  --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n  --output-format stream-json \\\n  --verbose\n```\n- Stream-json outputs one JSON object per line\n- Dispatcher parses each line in real-time\n- Results broadcast to WebSocket clients instantly\n\n### B. **Token Persistence**\nCurrent change: Token now saved to `data/.access_token` so it survives server restarts\n- First run: generates random 16-byte URL-safe token\n- Subsequent runs: reads from file\n- Can be overridden with `CC_TOKEN` environment variable\n\n### C. **Error Detection Improvement**\nCurrent change: Parse Claude's `result.is_error` field instead of relying only on exit code\n- Claude CLI sometimes returns non-zero exit even on success\n- Stream-json result object contains `is_error` boolean\n- More reliable failure detection\n\n### D. **WebSocket Real-Time Updates**\n- Two WebSocket endpoints: task logs + global events\n- Callbacks registered/unregistered dynamically\n- Dead callbacks cleaned up to prevent leaks\n- Toast notifications on status changes\n\n### E. **Safe File Browsing**\n- Path traversal prevention: resolve and check within PROJECT_DIR\n- File size limit: 100KB (larger files direct to SSH)\n- Breadcrumb navigation for context\n\n---\n\n## 10. UNIMPLEMENTED / FUTURE FEATURES\n\nBased on CLAUDE.md and PROGRESS.md:\n\n1. **Multi-instance parallelization** (MAX_WORKERS > 1)\n   - Worktree manager prepared but not used\n   - Worker slot management needed in dispatcher\n   \n2. **Plan Mode** (two-stage execution)\n   - Status: `planning` → `plan_review` states exist\n   - Needs: First Claude call to generate plan, user approval, second call to execute\n   \n3. **Service Worker caching** (PWA enhancement)\n   - Prepared in manifest but not implemented\n   \n4. **Database migrations** (for future schema changes)\n   - Currently only creates table if not exists\n\n---\n\n## 11. CRITICAL FILES FOR MODIFICATION\n\nIf you need to understand how to extend this system:\n\n1. **To add new API endpoints:** Edit `server.py` (add @app.post/@app.get routes)\n2. **To change task logic:** Edit `dispatcher.py` (modify execute_task function)\n3. **To add UI features:** Edit `static/index.html` (add HTML, CSS, JS)\n4. **To add database fields:** Edit `database.py` (CREATE TABLE) + migrations\n5. **To change configuration:** Edit `config.py` (environment variables)\n6. **To support multi-instance:** Edit `dispatcher.py` + `worktree_manager.py` (worker pool management)\n\n---\n\n## 12. FULL FILE PATHS (ABSOLUTE)\n\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/config.py`\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/database.py`\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/dispatcher.py`\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/server.py`\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/worktree_manager.py`\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/static/index.html`\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/data/tasks.db` (SQLite)\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/data/.access_token` (10 bytes: token)\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/logs/` (task execution logs)\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/backups/` (hourly DB backups)\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/requirements.txt`\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/setup.sh`\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/CLAUDE.md`\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/PROGRESS.md`\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/QUICKSTART.md`\n- `/home/ubuntu/cc-web-manager/PROMPTS.md`\n\n---\n\nThis is a complete, production-ready system for running Claude Code tasks remotely from a mobile phone. The architecture is clean, async-first, and designed for future scaling to multi-instance parallelization."}],"totalDurationMs":78950,"totalTokens":62001,"totalToolUseCount":25,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1646,"cache_read_input_tokens":55021,"output_tokens":5328,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1